  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Babies aged 0 to 90 days with a suspected infection requiring treatment with vancomycin will
      be recruited. They will be randomised to receive vancomycin as an intermittent infusion
      (over 1 hour) or as a continuous infusion (over 24 hours). The hypothesis is that
      administering vancomycin as a continuous infusion will result in improved attainment of
      target concentrations in blood at steady state (when the drug is in equilibrium) compared to
      intermittent infusion.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
